nit:  VOLT_V on these sounds redundant (though maybe you have a requirement to have a _<units> on all the names.

Would you please to tell if there some concoerns about adding the unit?
or I prefer to let voltage sensor follow the naming rule same with other sensors, which has been commonly used in former Meta platform.
It's fine with me if that's what Meta wants.
This should be a BOARD_PRODUCT_NAME probe and not a PRODUCT_PRODUCT name.  We need to match off the specific board we've identified and not the overall system product.

This change has been revised.
The board config will be probed only when both BOARD_PRODUCT_NAME and PRODUCT_PRODUCT_NAME meets.
Thank you for the correction.
can you change these to use underscores to match the other files?
File name have been revised, thank you for correction.
LGTM

What does the MATCH_ONE accomplish in these?  There aren't many existing JSON files that use it and I'm having trouble deciphering what the `src/perform_probe.cpp` code means.  If we don't need this, I would suggest  we remove it.
If entity-manager found more than one device meets the probe condition, it may duplicated using the config and cause service crashed, adding "MATCH_ONE" can ensure the config only be probed once.
That would imply that we have a bug in either our EM config and/or eeprom programming, right?  Isnt it better to fail-fast so we fix this instead of turning it into something that is ignored?
It wouldn't failed with these 3 json configs which should only one matching fru for each board, I' ll remove these "MATCH ONE" config then re-verify.
It has been virified successfully without "MATCH ONE" config.

Update adc128d818 on fanboard and pmbus power module/mp5023 on medusa board
Maybe just limit the Scale here

The reason I didn't add them in same place is that the drscription of legacy.json shows that: "Don't add additional properties to this schema".

It seems like be more reasonable that added into a new json conf as some former commits.
Combine this discussion with Ed's feedback.

No mention whatsoever of this schema change in the commit message.  I'm guessing this needs its own commit and explanation.  dbus-sensors is a whole bunch of applications, this looks like it's just for PSUsensor, and probably should go with the other definitions for similar (vin_scale) types, not in its own file.

I can seperate the commit to platform json config and schema change if needed.

I'm confused that even these are similar to "InScaleFactor" or "iout1_Scale", the description of legacy.json didn't allow to add new properties in future development, the only way I can add addtional item is searching appropriate json which has been existed or creating a new one.
